<div id="review_3278876783" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3278876783" />
    <a title="Derrick" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/93081346-derrick"><img alt="Derrick" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627582237p2/93081346.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3278876783?book_show_action=true">Nov 10, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Derrick" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Derrick" href="/user/show/93081346-derrick">Derrick</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781982147" href="/book/show/58287829-lisey-s-story">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/93081346-derrick?shelf=king-books">king-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3278876783" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15683988084514775772">This book turned out to be quite an emotional ride especially towards the end. For about the first two thirds of the book, I had been thinking there&apos;s no way I&apos;m giving this book five stars! There were parts that I thought were just so long and drawn out and boring. This book is definitely a slow burner. The character of Lisey is immensely well developed. I was able to feel exactly what she was feeling right along with her! The action and emotion really ramps up through about the last third of t</span>
  <span id="freeText15683988084514775772" style="display:none">This book turned out to be quite an emotional ride especially towards the end. For about the first two thirds of the book, I had been thinking there's no way I'm giving this book five stars! There were parts that I thought were just so long and drawn out and boring. This book is definitely a slow burner. The character of Lisey is immensely well developed. I was able to feel exactly what she was feeling right along with her! The action and emotion really ramps up through about the last third of the book. As always, the imagery King created both in the real world and in the alternate world was wondrous! I don't always consider myself to be much of an emotional person. When a book makes me feel emotional, that's when I know for sure it's significant. In this particular edition, there's a really cool interview with Stephen King at the end. In it he states Lisey's Story is one of his favorite books he's written. After reading the book myself, it's simple to see why. King does a great job all around and the slow build is very well worth it in the end. Impossible for me not to like this story a lot!</span>
  <a data-text-id="15683988084514775772" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


